{
  "doc_id": "1851",
  "text": "Potential toxicological effects following exposure to titanium dioxide (TiO 2 ) are of current interest [CITATION_1] 2] . TiO 2 is a mineral pigment which, when used in a particulate form, is valued for its properties as a whitening or brightening agent, and is included in some processed foods (E171 on ingredients lists), toothpastes, capsules and tablets. From these sources, the average daily intake of pigment-grade TiO 2 for an adult in the UK is about [CITATION_2] 12 particles/day [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , nominally~0.04 mg/kg/day for a 70 kg adult. These findings are supported by a recent Dutch study with mean long term intakes of pigmentgrade TiO 2 ranging from 0.06 mg/kg/day in elderly subjects to 0.17 mg/kg/day for 7-69-year-olds [CITATION_5] . In 2-6 year old children, however, it was higher at 0.67 mg/kg/day [CITATION_6] .",
